# Subagent Contract (guardrail — required for plugin Agents (`agents/*.md`))

Subagents are specialized AI assistants Cursor's main agent can delegate to. Each subagent runs in its own context window and returns a result to the parent. To keep them maintainable and Ollama-portable, every shipped subagent MUST follow this contract.

## Required YAML frontmatter

- `name`: lowercase-hyphenated identifier (e.g. `pi-modbus-mailbox-inspector`, `hardware-doc-checker`).
- `description`: one sentence with a delegation trigger phrase ("use proactively", "use after", "use when …"). This drives Cursor's automatic delegation.
- `model`: one of `fast`, `inherit`, or a specific model id.

## Recommended frontmatter

- `readonly: true` for validators / verifiers / inspectors (no edits, no state-changing shell, no Modbus writes).
- `is_background: true` for long-running jobs (full pamphlet rebuilds, large `pytest` suites, full Modbus mailbox scans).

## Body rules

- Body ≤30 lines.
- Body must reference its **canonical skill** under `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` rather than duplicating procedure (single source of truth).
- Body must instruct the subagent to read repo-root `DEVELOPMENT-LOCAL.md` when present to resolve placeholders, and to ask when required inputs remain missing.
- Output format must be bounded — counts / OK-FAIL summaries / one-line-per-failure — never full HTML, full JSON, or full stack-trace dumps, and **never** a full Modbus map dump or full POU listing.
- Stop conditions: missing required input, allowlist-blocked command, output would be unbounded.

## Local-model (Ollama) variants

A project can drop a sibling file with a different model id and the same body, named `<name>.local.md`. The package sync overwrites by name only, so `*.local.md` siblings are preserved. See `DEVELOPMENT-LOCAL-OLLAMA.md` (when present in the consuming project).

## Anti-patterns (do not ship)

- Vague descriptions ("Use for general tasks") — Cursor's auto-delegation needs specificity.
- Overly long prompts (>1000 words) — slower, harder to maintain, no smarter.
- Duplicating an existing slash command or skill — use the existing artifact.
- A subagent that performs **Modbus writes** without an explicit `readonly: false` declaration AND an explicit authorization scope in the subagent body (see `15-subagent-delegation-guardrails.mdc`). The default for this plugin's subagents is read-only Modbus access.
